Request schema

Use something like this:

{
  "workflow": "new_payment",
  "userId": "user1",
  "sessionId": "sess-123",
  "tenantId": "tenantA",
  "slots": {
    "account": "abc.savings",
    "beneficiary": "jonh",
    "currency": "INR",
    "payment_method": "RTGS"
  }
}

Important:

the service should not need to know workflow internals
Python decides which slots to verify
the service only verifies the slots it receives
Response schema

Use something like this:

{
  "allVerified": false,
  "workflow": "new_payment",
  "results": {
    "account": {
      "verified": true,
      "exactMatch": true,
      "canonicalValue": "abc.savings",
      "suggestions": []
    },
    "beneficiary": {
      "verified": false,
      "exactMatch": false,
      "canonicalValue": null,
      "suggestions": [
        "john",
        "johnny"
      ]
    }
  }
}

Fields:

allVerified = true only if every slot passed
verified = slot accepted or not
exactMatch = direct match or fuzzy/derived
canonicalValue = normalized final value
suggestions = close alternatives
Error response schema

Use a consistent error response like:

{
  "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
  "message": "Request validation failed",
  "details": {
    "userId": "must not be blank"
  }
}
Exception handling design

Use both:

exception package

Contains custom exception classes only:

ResolutionException
DataSourceException
ResourceNotFoundException
ValidationException
advice package

Contains global exception handler:

GlobalExceptionHandler

This handler should catch exceptions and map them to API responses.

Also handle validation exceptions like:

MethodArgumentNotValidException
Coding best practices

Follow these rules:

constructor injection only
use @RequiredArgsConstructor
avoid field injection
use record for DTOs where possible
avoid System.out.println
use LoggerFactory
validate at the API boundary with @Valid
keep controller thin
keep service pure and business-focused
keep datasource responsible only for data access
Security / ops / resilience

These are desired eventually, but not first-day blockers:

correlation ID filter
auth filter / API key
Actuator
Prometheus metrics
Resilience4j retry
circuit breaker
timeout
OpenAPI/Swagger

The service should be stateless and horizontally scalable.

